Paper: hep-th/9901097

Date: 1999-01-21

Title: Hamilton-Jacobi treatment of fields with constraints

Authors: Dumitru Baleanu (Bogoliubov LTPh,JINR, Dubna, Russia), Yurdahan Guler

(Cankaya University,Ankara,Turkey)Comments: 7 pages LaTeX, corrected typos

Journal-ref: Nuovo Cim. B115 (2000) 25-31

In this paper the $Guler's$ formalism for the systems with finite degrees offreedom is applied to the field theories with constraints. The integrabilityconditions are investigated and the path integral quantization is performedusing the action given by Hamilton-Jacobi formulation. The Proca's model isinvestigated in details.